medi:segment.name: Beginning of message
medi:segment.medi:documentation: BGM, A segment to indicate the message name, type, number and functionality.

medi:segment.name: Date/time/period
medi:segment.medi:documentation: DTM, A segment to indicate the date/time of message creation and the date and time of cargo report to Customs.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 1: A group of segments to identify the unique reference number and date time details for the whole message.

medi:segment.name: Reference
medi:segment.medi:documentation: RFF, A segment to provide the unique reference number for the message, e.g. manifest number.

medi:segment.name: Date/time/period
medi:segment.medi:documentation: DTM, A segment to indicate the date/time of the reference number for the message.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 2: A group of segments to identify contact and communication contact information related to the person responsible for the cargo reporting.

medi:segment.name: Name and address
medi:segment.medi:documentation: NAD, A segment to identify the person or party reporting the cargo.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 3: A group of segments to identify a contact and its communication related party.

medi:segment.name: Contact information
medi:segment.medi:documentation: CTA, A segment to identify a person or department within a party.

medi:segment.name: Communication contact
medi:segment.medi:documentation: COM, A segment to identify the communication numbers of persons or department to whom communication should be directed.

medi:segment.name: Free text
medi:segment.medi:documentation: FTX, A segment to provide reason for change in report.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 4: A group of segments to identify details of transport, locations and associated dates/times.

medi:segment.name: Details of transport
medi:segment.medi:documentation: TDT, A segment to identify the primary identity of the conveyance e.g. voyage/flight number, vehicle number, railway car initials and numbers and name of vessel reference number.

medi:segment.name: Place/location identification
medi:segment.medi:documentation: LOC, A segment to indicate locations relevant to the details of transport, such as port/place of loading, port/place of discharge and port/place of initial arrival.

medi:segment.name: Date/time/period
medi:segment.medi:documentation: DTM, A segment to specify dates/times related to details of transport.

medi:segment.name: General indicator
medi:segment.medi:documentation: GIS, A segment to specify the various customs processing indicators for the whole message.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 5: A group of segments to specify details of the equipment including information related to measurement, dimensions, seals, empty container responsible party, container quarantine indicator, as well as temperature/range and use indicator.

medi:segment.name: Equipment details
medi:segment.medi:documentation: EQD, A segment to specify the type of equipment, empty container indicator, and container number.

medi:segment.name: Transport service requirements
medi:segment.medi:documentation: TSR, A segment to specify the contract, carriage conditions, service and priority requirements for the transport.

medi:segment.name: Measurements
medi:segment.medi:documentation: MEA, A segment to specify the measurements details for the equipment.

medi:segment.name: Dimensions
medi:segment.medi:documentation: DIM, A segment to specify the dimensions.

medi:segment.name: Seal number
medi:segment.medi:documentation: SEL, A segment to specify the seal number.

medi:segment.name: Name and address
medi:segment.medi:documentation: NAD, A segment to specify the name and address of the empty container responsible party.

medi:segment.name: General indicator
medi:segment.medi:documentation: GIS, A segment to specify the container quarantine indicator.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 6: A group of segments to indicate temperature information.

medi:segment.name: Temperature
medi:segment.medi:documentation: TMP, A segment to specify temperature settings and indicator that refrigeration is in use.

medi:segment.name: Range details
medi:segment.medi:documentation: RNG, A segment to specify a range of temperatures to be maintained on refrigeration equipment.

medi:segment.name: Control total
medi:segment.medi:documentation: CNT, A segment to specify the total number of masters bills in the message.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 7: A group of segments to provide details of the consignment(s).

medi:segment.name: Consignment information
medi:segment.medi:documentation: CNI, A segment to sequentially number master bills reported in a multi-consignment message. For a single consignment message, this sequence number will always be 1.

medi:segment.name: Control total
medi:segment.medi:documentation: CNT, A segment to specify the total number of house bills reported under one master bill.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 8: SG14 A group of segments specifying the details of each consignment.

medi:segment.name: Reference
medi:segment.medi:documentation: RFF, A segment to identify the bill number referring to the appropriate type of bill (e.g. master bill of lading, house bill of lading, straight air waybill).

medi:segment.name: Control total
medi:segment.medi:documentation: CNT, A segment to specify total consignment quantity and weight.

medi:segment.name: Monetary amount
medi:segment.medi:documentation: MOA, A segment to specify the onward carriage shipment value, amount of insurance, value of Customs in-bond movement, declared value for Customs, declared value for carriage, no Customs value, transport charge amount, freight payment amount.

medi:segment.name: Place/location identification
medi:segment.medi:documentation: LOC, A segment to specify the Customs clearance office/place, place of origin of carriage, place of acceptance by importing carrier, place of ultimate destination of goods, place of transhipment, place of departure, place of customs examination and place/port of discharge.

medi:segment.name: General indicator
medi:segment.medi:documentation: GIS, A segment to specify processing indicators such as import/export/transit indicator, container quarantine indicator, onward movement type indicator and status of the goods.

medi:segment.name: Currencies
medi:segment.medi:documentation: CUX, A segment to specify the default currency for the consignment, e.g. air waybill currency.

medi:segment.name: Charge payment instructions
medi:segment.medi:documentation: CPI, A segment to specify the cargo category type, e.g. weight valuation, prepaid/collect and method of payment.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 9: A group of segments to identify details of onward carriage for each consignment.

medi:segment.name: Details of transport
medi:segment.medi:documentation: TDT, A segment to specify the identity of the onward conveyance.

medi:segment.name: Place/location identification
medi:segment.medi:documentation: LOC, A segment to indicate locations relevant to the onward transport of the goods.

medi:segment.name: Date/time/period
medi:segment.medi:documentation: DTM, A segment to specify dates/times related to details of onward transport.

medi:segment.name: Measurements
medi:segment.medi:documentation: MEA, A segment to specify physical measurements, including dimension tolerances, weights and counts (e.g. vehicle weight details).

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 10: A group of segments to provide booking details (reference and type).

medi:segment.name: Reference
medi:segment.medi:documentation: RFF, A segment to specify onward carriage control number, onward carriage bond number and secondary conveyance identification numbers.

medi:segment.name: Transport service requirements
medi:segment.medi:documentation: TSR, A segment to specify the contract and carriage conditions and service and priority requirements for the transport.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 11: A group of segments to identify the parties, contacts and related references and dates.

medi:segment.name: Name and address
medi:segment.medi:documentation: NAD, A segment specifying the name and address of the consignor, shipper, notifier, consignee, empty container responsible party, nominated reporting agent, railway issuing waybill, and reporting party.

medi:segment.name: Date/time/period
medi:segment.medi:documentation: DTM, A segment to specify date and/or time or period related to the party(s) identified in the NAD segment (e.g. date of birth).

medi:segment.name: Reference
medi:segment.medi:documentation: RFF, A segment to identify a reference used by a party e.g. reporting party's reference number.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 12: A group of segments identifying a contact and its communication related to the party.

medi:segment.name: Contact information
medi:segment.medi:documentation: CTA, A segment to identify a person or department within a party.

medi:segment.name: Communication contact
medi:segment.medi:documentation: COM, A segment to identify the communication numbers of persons or department to whom communication should be directed.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 13: A group of segments to specify, at the consignment level, the quantity manifested, quantity landed and reason for change.

medi:segment.name: Quantity
medi:segment.medi:documentation: QTY, A segment identifying quantity manifested and quantity landed.

medi:segment.name: Free text
medi:segment.medi:documentation: FTX, A segment to indicate the reason for change e.g. part/short/overshipped cargo.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 14: CST-SG15-SG16 A group of segments specifying goods item details including number and type of packages, handling instructions, quantity variances, package identification, goods description, monetary amounts, measurements, indicators for split goods placement, indicator for dangerous goods, status of the goods, documents.

medi:segment.name: Goods item details
medi:segment.medi:documentation: GID, A segment identifying the line item number, as well as number and type of packages.

medi:segment.name: Package
medi:segment.medi:documentation: PAC, A segment identifying the level of packaging.

medi:segment.name: Handling instructions
medi:segment.medi:documentation: HAN, A segment identifying handling instructions.

medi:segment.name: Free text
medi:segment.medi:documentation: FTX, A segment to identify the description of goods.

medi:segment.name: Measurements
medi:segment.medi:documentation: MEA, A segment to identify the goods item gross/net weight.

medi:segment.name: Monetary amount
medi:segment.medi:documentation: MOA, Values per item.

medi:segment.name: Split goods placement
medi:segment.medi:documentation: SGP, A segment to indicate the placement of goods in one or more containers.

medi:segment.name: Dangerous goods
medi:segment.medi:documentation: DGS, A segment to identify dangerous goods.

medi:segment.name: Package identification
medi:segment.medi:documentation: PCI, A segment identifying shipping marks.

medi:segment.name: Customs status of goods
medi:segment.medi:documentation: CST, A segment to identify Harmonized System codes related to each goods item.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 15: A group of segments specifying general indicators, associated date/time details and documentary requirements.

medi:segment.name: General indicator
medi:segment.medi:documentation: GIS, A segment to indicate other government requirements (e.g. government quarantine indicator) to be met prior to onward movement and status of the goods.

medi:segment.name: Date/time/period
medi:segment.medi:documentation: DTM, A segment to specify a date/time related to the whole group.

medi:segment.name: Document/message details
medi:segment.medi:documentation: DOC, A segment to indicate other government agency documentary requirements which must be met prior to onward movement.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 16: A group of segments to specify, at goods item level, the quantity manifested, quantity landed and reason for change.

medi:segment.name: Quantity
medi:segment.medi:documentation: QTY, A segment identifying quantity manifested and quantity landed.

medi:segment.name: Free text
medi:segment.medi:documentation: FTX, A segment to indicate the reason for change e.g. part/short/overshipped cargo.

medi:segmentGroup.medi:documentation: Segment group 17: A group of segments to specify the authentication of the message.

medi:segment.name: Authentication result
medi:segment.medi:documentation: AUT, A segment to specify the results of the application of an authentication procedure, including the authenticity of sender to ensure integrity of data.

medi:segment.name: Date/time/period
medi:segment.medi:documentation: DTM, A segment to specify the date/time/period when a message is authenticated.

medi:segment.name: Reference
medi:segment.medi:documentation: RFF, A segment to indicate any references to the authentication process.
